Thanks for the response. It happened when I load the pretrained and converted graph as
`
        with tf.gfile.FastGFile(model_path, 'rb') as f:
            graph_def = tf.GraphDef()
            graph_def.ParseFromString(f.read())
            _ = tf.import_graph_def(graph_def, name='')
`
and then run the session
`
            correct += np.sum(sesh.run(top_k_op,
                                       feed_dict={input_node: images,
                                                  label_node: labels}))
`
Does it mean I have to update the the graph (.pb) file? Thanks.
